The paper deals with facial landmark detection using deep learning, which falls under computer vision (cs.CV). The proposed method involves introducing a latent variable and optimizing it, which is a common technique in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also mentions the use of a global heatmap correction unit, which is a technique used in multimedia (cs.MM) and human-computer interaction (cs.HC).
